netic technologies is a game changer. To explore its implications, conservation scientist Kent Redford and geographer Bill Adams turn to synthetic biology, ecological restoration, political ecology, and de-extinction studies. They propose a way forward for conservation and provide a much-needed vision for protecting nature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aBiodiversity conservation. 0aSynthetic biology. 7aNATURE / Environmental Conservation & Protection.2bisacsh1 aAdams, William M., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2021 Englishz978311075414808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2021z9783110753912oZDB-23-DPM08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073923740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300258677423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300258677.jpg  a978-3-11-073923-7  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075414-8  EBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2021 Englishb2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  aZDB-23-DPMb2021